Package: SamplingCoordination
Type: Package
Title: Coordination of Samples for Complex Rotative Designs
Version: 1.0.1
Author: José Zea <jfzeac@unal.edu.co>,
    Hugo Andres Gutierrez Rojas <andres.gutierrez@cepal.org>,
    Stalyn Guerrero <syguerrerog@unal.edu.co>
    Yury Vanessa Ochoa Montes <yury.ochoa@urosario.edu.co>
Maintainer: Hugo Andres Gutierrez Rojas <andres.gutierrez@cepal.org>
Description: Provides tools for the coordination and management of samples
    in complex rotative survey designs. Implements methods for rotating panels,
    overlap control between successive samples, Poisson and Pareto coordination,
    simple random sampling coordination (SI), and redistribution of primary
    sampling units (PSU). Designed for use in household and social surveys
    that require controlled sample renewal across periods.
License: GPL (>= 2)
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    dplyr,
    magrittr,
    rlang,
    TeachingSampling
Suggests:
    tidyverse
Depends:
    R (>= 3.5)
LazyData: true
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
